Base.Explanation: Create a contact in Active Directory. The contact is created in a Active Directory domain, organizational unit or other container. Optionally, you can specify the domain controller on which the user creation is created.

ArrayElement.Name: Domain
ArrayElement.Description: The name of the domain (DNS or NETBIOS style, e.g. tools4ever.com or TOOLS4EVER) where the contact will be created. Optionally you can specify the property 'Organizational Unit-Container'. If you specify a value for this property, do not specify a value for property 'LDAP-container' since this specification takes precedence.

ArrayElement.Name: Organizational Unit-Container
ArrayElement.Description: The name of the Organizational Unit-Container where the contact must be created (example: Students or Students\Group1). If you specify a value for this property, you should also specify a value for the 'Domain' property. If you specify a value for this property, do not specify a value for property 'LDAP-container' since that specification overrules this specification.

ArrayElement.Name: LDAP Container
ArrayElement.Description: The LDAP name of the organizational unit or container where the contact must be created (example: cn=Users, cn=Tools4ever, cn=Com). You must specify either a value for this property or values for the properties 'Domain' and 'Organizational Unit-Container'. If values for both methods are specified, this method takes precedence.

ArrayElement.Name: Domain (controller)
ArrayElement.Description: Optional: The name of the domain controller or domain, used to access to the domain, container or organizational unit where the contact must be created. If this value is not specified or the name of a domain is specified, the application creates the account on a domain controller that is to be determined by Active Directory (serverless binding). If a domain controller is specified, the account is explicitly created on the specified controller (server binding). In both cases, Active Directory will replicate the account information to all domain controllers in the Active Directory forests and domains.

ArrayElement.Name: Name generation algorithm
ArrayElement.Description: The algorithm used to generate the 'Common Name' of the contact. The 'Common Name' of the contact needs to be unique in the Organizational Unit where it is created. In general the variables %FirstName%, %MiddleName% and %LastName% are used to generate values for the variable %FullName% which is assigned to the 'Common Name' attribute of the contact.

ArrayElement.Name: CommonName
ArrayElement.Description: The 'CommonName' corresponds with the 'Common Name' of the contact. This name defines the contact in an Organizational Unit and must be unique. You can use property 'Name generation algorithm' to make the name unique automatically.

ArrayElement.Name: DisplayName
ArrayElement.Description: The 'DisplayName' in most cases corresponds with the common name of the contact.

ArrayElement.Name: Given-name
ArrayElement.Description: The Given-name corresponds with the first name of the contact. The Given-name is an optional attribute of Active Directory contacts.

ArrayElement.Name: Initials
ArrayElement.Description: The 'Initials'-field name corresponds with the middle name of the contact. The 'Initials'-field is an optional attribute of Active Directory contacts.

ArrayElement.Name: Surname
ArrayElement.Description: The 'Surname' corresponds with the last name of the contact. The 'Surname' is an optional attribute of Active Directory contacts.

ArrayElement.Name: Description
ArrayElement.Description: A contact comment. The field can contain a text of any length.

ArrayElement.Name: General - Office
ArrayElement.Description: This is the person's office location, including the building and office address or number.

ArrayElement.Name: General - Telephone number
ArrayElement.Description: The person's phone number.

ArrayElement.Name: General - E-mail
ArrayElement.Description: The person's e-mail address. The e-mail address appears with the universal principal name suffix (for example, someone@microsoft.com).

ArrayElement.Name: General - Web-page
ArrayElement.Description: The person's home page URL, either on the Internet or in the local intranet site.

ArrayElement.Name: Address - Street
ArrayElement.Description: The person's street address in this space.

ArrayElement.Name: Address - P.O. Box
ArrayElement.Description: The person's Post Office box number in this space.

ArrayElement.Name: Address - City
ArrayElement.Description: The city where this person is located.

ArrayElement.Name: Address - State/province
ArrayElement.Description: The state or province where this person is located.

ArrayElement.Name: Address - Zip/Postal Code
ArrayElement.Description: The zip or postal code applicable for the person.

ArrayElement.Name: Address - Country/region
ArrayElement.Description: This person's country or region

ArrayElement.Name: Telephone number - home
ArrayElement.Description: The home telephone number for this person.

ArrayElement.Name: Telephone number - pager
ArrayElement.Description: The pager number for this person.

ArrayElement.Name: Telephone number - mobile
ArrayElement.Description: The mobile or cellular phone number for this user.

ArrayElement.Name: Telephone number - fax
ArrayElement.Description: The person's fax machine number here.

ArrayElement.Name: Telephone number - IP phone
ArrayElement.Description: This person's IP telephony number.

ArrayElement.Name: Telephone - Notes
ArrayElement.Description: Descriptive information to add any comments for this person.

ArrayElement.Name: Organization - Department
ArrayElement.Description: The department for this person

ArrayElement.Name: Organization - Title
ArrayElement.Description: The title for this person

ArrayElement.Name: Organization - Company
ArrayElement.Description: The company for this person

ArrayElement.Name: Contact Object
ArrayElement.Description: An internal data structure representing the contact. This property is an 'output only' property and is generated automatically. This property can be used in other script actions, for instance to create Exchange addresses and setup groupmemberships.

Base.Explanation: Get the value of an attribute of an Active Directory object, for instance a user account. The attribute is specified by the LDAP display name of the attribute. For the most common properties, the LDAP name can be selected from a list.

ArrayElement.Name: User Object
ArrayElement.Description: A data structure representing a user account. If you want to obtain the property of a user account object, you can use this property to specify the Active Directory object for this action. Use the action 'Get user (AD)' to find the user account in Active Directory and setup the variable that contains the 'User Object'.

ArrayElement.Name: Active Directory Object
ArrayElement.Description: A data structure representing a Active Directory object for which an attribute must obtained. This property can only be used as a input variable. Earlier in the script, another script action must have generated the value for this variable.

ArrayElement.Name: LDAP attribute display name
ArrayElement.Description: The LDAP name of the attribute. The name identifies the attribute of the Active Directory object. For a number of well-known attributes, the LDAP name can be selected from a list but you can specify any other valid name.

ArrayElement.Name: Multi-value flag
ArrayElement.Description: Save multi-values as multi-values for the attribute. If set to 'Yes' and the attribute is multi-valued, the values are stored as multi-values (text list or table). If set to 'No' and the attribute is multi-valued, the values are converted into a single value. Default value: 'No'.

ArrayElement.Name: Convert to text flag
ArrayElement.Description: Convert the value(s) of the attribute to text. Default value: 'Yes'. If set, depending on property 'Multi-value flag', the result is either a single text or text list. If not set ('No'), the results is stored as one of the UMRA supported data types.

ArrayElement.Name: Error if no attribute found
ArrayElement.Description: Generate an error for this script action if the specified attribute is not found.

ArrayElement.Name: Error if empty
ArrayElement.Description: Generate an error for this script action if the attribute is found but attribute value is empty.

ArrayElement.Name: Attribute value
ArrayElement.Description: The value found for the attribute. This property is an 'output only' property and is generated by the application automatically. By default, the value for this property is stored in variable %AttributeValue%.
